b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48544.htm)  [Next](sbe48546.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n9\\. On the passing away of the effected (world of Brahma), together with its\nruler, (the souls go) to what is higher than that; on account of scriptural\ndeclaration.\n\nOn the passing away of the effected world of Brahma, together with its ruler\nHira _n_ yagarbha, who then recognises his qualification for higher knowledge,\nthe soul also which had gone to Hira _n_ yagarbha attains to true knowledge\nand thus reaches Brahman, which is higher than that,\n\np. 750\n\ni.e. higher than the effected world of Brahma. This is known from the texts\ndeclaring that he who proceeds on the path of light reaches immortality and\ndoes not return; and is further confirmed by the text, 'They all, reaching the\nhighest immortality, become free in the world of Brahman (Brahma) at the time\nof the great end ' (Mu. Up. III, 2, 6).\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 10. And on account of Smriti](sbe48546.htm)\n\n"